Students sing the lead role at the zhejiang university academic annual conference The research results make people's minds open - Xinhua Net
Wash your hands with air, judge diseases with a breath, and accurately search for the source of smog Yesterday evening, at the opening ceremony of the 2016 Academic Annual Conference of Zhejiang University, a series of brain-opening academic achievements were commended.
The main researchers of these achievements are students, the research covers the environment, machinery, energy, medical, life sciences, humanities education and other major fields, students from a curious idea, created a lot of high-end inventions with application value, some of which have won awards at home and abroad.
Biosensors: Your family medical examiner
The team of Zhang Diming, a doctoral student in the School of Biomedical Engineering, demonstrated a biosensor on the smart phone side, which is only half the size of a smart phone.
"You only need to take a light breath, and this set of instruments can initially detect the health of your body from the gas components you exhale. ”
Zhang Diming said that this set of sensors is connected to the smartphone, and after exhaling the gas, the health report will be displayed on the mobile phone.
Smart bracelets on the market that can detect health status generally detect physical parameters such as temperature and pulse.
This biosensor uses graphene, a new material, which targets chemical elements and a keen sense of smell that allows it to reflect the health of the body more deeply and accurately.
Smart Surgical Lights: High-energy eyes for doctors
In addition to smartphones, smart surgical lights are also used in the operating room.
This invention won a silver medal at the 44th International Exhibition of Inventions in Geneva, Switzerland, this year.
The team of Zhu Linjing and Shen Junfei, master's students in the School of Optoelectronic Science and Engineering, opened up new ideas in the defects of traditional surgical lamps and invented intelligent LED surgical shadowless lamps.
"The early detection and resection of many diseases are not in place, which is related to the lamp used in the doctor's operating room. ”
Shen Junfei said that for example, in the early examination of cancer, if the doctor cannot see all the tumor tissue in time, then the cancer cells will spread later.
This intelligent surgical lamp has four lamp plates that enhance the differentiation of different tissues under light by adjusting the spectrum.
During the operation, the doctor can adjust the size, brightness, spectrum, color uniformity and imagelessness of the spot at any time according to the needs of the operation and personal habits.
This intelligent surgical lamp has been tried in hospitals such as Run Run Shaw Hospital affiliated to Zhejiang University School of Medicine and Children's Hospital Affiliated to Zhejiang University School of Medicine, and has received good feedback.
Last October, the invention won the first prize of the National Challenge Cup.
Wash your hands with air: water-saving and cool
Ordinary people wash their hands with water, at most rub some soap, squeeze some hand sanitizer, and Li Qizhang and other students have invented a set of "air hand washing device".
Just by standing on the handwashing station, our weight can compress the air out.
"It's like a pump.
The compressed air, which forms a fluid at the tap, is combined with the water.
That way, we can wash our hands! ”
Color development reactions and bacterial residue experiments have proved that the effect of hand washing by this method is the same as that of ordinary hand washing methods.
This device only needs to rely on our own gravity as a drive, which can not only ensure the degree of washing, but also save 90% of the water, the whole process is completely energy-free, energy-saving and environmentally friendly.
Last year, at the second Global Challenges Summit, the invention stood out from many of the world's top universities and won the only gold medal.
Chongqing Secondary Vocational School Pilot Modern Apprenticeship System Admission is a prospective employee of the enterprise - Xinhua Net
Yesterday, the reporter learned from the Municipal Education Commission that starting this year, the city will pilot the "modern apprenticeship system" talent training model in 60 secondary vocational schools, and the students who accept the pilot training also have apprenticeship status, and the pilot enterprises will be pre-admitted as unit employees after enrollment entry.
The Municipal Education Commission requires that the enrollment and admission of secondary vocational schools and the employment procedures of enterprises be standardized, the dual identity of apprentices of secondary vocational school students and prospective employees of enterprises be clarified, in accordance with the principle of two-way selection, apprentices, schools and enterprises sign a tripartite agreement, and for apprentices who have reached the age of 16 but have not reached the age of 18, an agreement must be signed by the apprentice, guardian, school and enterprise to determine the rights and interests of all parties and the specific positions, teaching content, and rights and interests protection of apprentices on the job.
Pilot schools are encouraged to use the modern apprenticeship system to jointly carry out pre-job training and transfer training for enterprise employees with cooperative enterprises.
Pilot schools should reform the talent training model.
Schools and enterprises jointly design talent training programs, and jointly formulate professional teaching standards, curriculum standards, post standards, enterprise master standards, quality control standards and corresponding implementation plans.
The pilot takes the training system as a pilot cycle, and the internship time of students in enterprises is determined according to the professional talent training program, and the top internship is generally 6 months.
In enterprise practice, the enterprise team management model should be implemented, according to the characteristics of different majors, 1 master can bring 2 to 5 apprentices to form a study group to ensure that students are proficient in the skills required for each rotation position.
According to the arrangement, from 2016 to August 2019, the city identified 60 municipal intermediate vocational modern apprenticeship pilots in three batches, with each pilot number of about 50 people, and a total of about 3,000 students (apprentices) were trained.
In accordance with the principle of piloting first and then implementing, and gradually advancing from point to point, explore the establishment of a long-term mechanism for joint enrollment, joint training, and integrated education between schools and enterprises, effectively improve students' job skills, and improve the employment rate and employment quality of students.
