South African doctor: Although the transmissibility of Aomi Kerong is strong, it is mostly mild
Many doctors and medical experts in South Africa believe that the new coronavirus Omilton variant is less severe than the Delta variant, although it spreads more quickly.
As the Aumechjong variant spreads in South Africa, an organization of more than five thousand doctors in South Africa's Gauteng province reported that the symptoms of covid-19 patients they are currently treating are mild, such as body aches and coughs, similar to the flu, according to the Associated Press.
Dr. Unben Pillay, the group's director, said he sees dozens of patients a day, but none need to be hospitalized yet.
Pillay said: "They are able to control the disease at home, and most people recover within 10 to 14 days of isolation . ”
This includes elderly patients and those with health problems, which would otherwise be more likely to be severely ill from coronavirus infection, he said.
In contrast, he said, in the last wave of the Delta outbreak, the COVID-19 patients he treated had "difficulty breathing and low blood oxygen levels."
Many people are hospitalized within a few days."
Within two weeks of the first report of the Omiljung mutant strain in southern Africa, other doctors shared similar experiences.
While it will take weeks to collect enough data, doctors' observations and early evidence provide some clues.
According to the National Institute of Infectious Diseases in South Africa, only 30% of the COVID-19 patients hospitalized in recent weeks are serious diseases, which is half the proportion of severe diseases in the previous wave; The average length of hospital stay has been reduced from 8 days to 2.8 days; only 3% of recent COVID-19 patients have died, compared with 20% of deaths in early outbreaks in South Africa.
Willem Hanekom, director of the African Institute of Health, cites data from the National Institute of Infectious Diseases and other reports: "At the moment, almost all indications are that this is a milder disease . ”
He also said: "It's still early, and we need to get the data later.
Usually, hospitalizations and deaths occur later, and we enter this wave of outbreaks for only two weeks. ”
Meanwhile, scientists around the world are looking at the number of cases and hospitalization rates while testing the effectiveness of current vaccines and treatments.
Although Delta remains the world's leading strain of COVID-19, cases of Omiljung are emerging in dozens of countries, with South Africa at the epicenter of the outbreak.
According to health officials, the number of new cases detected in Gauteng in the first week of December increased by 400 percent, and tests showed that the Omiljung variant accounted for more than 90 percent of cases.
Education Review: What does it take to save abducted children?
If we draw an analogy to the famous public service slogan "No sale, no killing", then, in a good environment without the demand for "abduction", mass prevention and mass governance and the whole people's anti-abduction make abduction and trafficking unprofitable, risky and costly, and such crimes will not occur repeatedly.
Recently, the Criminal Investigation Bureau of the Ministry of Public Security launched an emergency release platform for missing children developed by the Anti-Abduction Office.
This is an Internet information platform created to establish an authoritative channel for the release of missing children and to recover abducted children in a timely manner.
Hearing that this app is called "Reunion", I feel warm and warm.
The new technology means are not only called "literature and art" and full of feelings, but also use information properly, practically and effectively.
The primary goal of cracking down on abduction and law enforcement is to recover abducted children and protect their personal safety and freedom.
The second is the trial and punishment of suspects.
The meaning of criminal punishment, from individual punishment and social prevention to legal education, can be listed in many "big words".
However, until the abduction and trafficking case is broken, priority should be given to the personal safety of the victims.
Under the urgent purpose of "seeking help", topics such as "whether the abduction and trafficking of children should be executed all the time" can be put aside and discussed cautiously; But the rescue of abducted children cannot wait.
Based on the experience of investigating such cases, traffickers are accustomed to staying away from the crime site as soon as possible after they have succeeded.
If the abduction operation is delayed for one minute, the child may be one step away from the parents, and the difficulty of solving the case will increase by one point.
In this case, it is indeed a pragmatic action to come up with effective methods such as the "reunion" platform that directly help to solve the case and find the child.
After all, "cracking down on abduction" is a big task that requires the operation of the entire legal system to do a good job.
Cracking down on crime and protecting the rights and interests of children and parents, from the improvement of legislation to the protection of the judiciary and the meticulousness of law enforcement, there is no need to implement the care of "protecting the young and helping the weak".
In addition, the prevention of child trafficking, from the family to society, can be done better.
For example, in a common case, a family of three rested at the train station, and the parents were asleep, and they woke up to find that the child was missing.
A two-year-old child cannot be expected to have sufficient self-protection skills, but as a parent of a young child, you should at least have a considerable sense of protection.
Two parents taking turns resting, or keeping their children under safe protection, are the minimum means of preventing children from being abducted.
From the other side of the police crackdown on trafficking, the party who buys abducted children should also be paid attention to and punished.
A single wrongdoer is often just one link in a long chain.
According to the Provisions of our Criminal Code, the statutory penalty for the crime of trafficking in children is 5 years; If the circumstances are particularly serious, the death penalty may be imposed and the confiscation of property shall be imposed.
With a high starting point and a maximum punishment, the crime of child abduction and trafficking is obviously a crime with heavier punishments under the general trend of "light punishment".
However, there are still many cases of abduction and trafficking every year.
It can be seen that some people have backward concepts in raising children and have a weak sense of law.
The legal education of this group of people should be followed up simultaneously.
To effectively control the crime of trafficking, we cannot rely solely on strict official law enforcement.
If the "market" for abduction and trafficking exists extensively, and the traffickers are eager for profit, constantly innovate the means of abduction and trafficking, and form a "fighting method" situation with law enforcers, the anti-abduction operation is bound to fall into the quagmire of inefficiency.
Therefore, breaking down backward concepts and popularizing legal knowledge will also help to eradicate the crime of abduction, trafficking and bribery of children.
