Don't scare people down at the starting line - Xinhua Net
When visiting the book market, you can often feel the popularity of successful books.
Many of today's success books preach the "best principle"—that is, to assume or imply that you can "do it" and then tell you what you need to do.— "what."
It is equivalent to saying that it has suddenly crossed the most important and fundamental link of "how to do it".
Because of this, these books all have a common feature —either they do their best in a single blow, or they do nothing at all; Either 100 or 0; Either you climb Mount Taishan, or you simply stay where you are.
This "best principle" makes anyone look at it and admit that it is "incomparable", but 99% of people will be intimidated by the starting line.
Because this theory advocates a path of "you have to make up your mind, be a new person, and make a 180-degree transformation", which is precisely the fatal weakness of many people.
For those who stick to the rules, conform to the old ways, and refuse to change, you have to shout "you want to change" in his ear, which is undoubtedly a self-deception and a move to play the piano to the cow.
The vast majority of people will be timid in front of the word "transformation", stagnant, and difficult to make up their minds; Or with a momentary impulse to make a determination to "change" and bravely take the first step, but often the good times are not long, and they can't persist for a while before they lose, and it is difficult to see sustainability.
Mr. Ma Sanli's famous cross-talk of "Starting from Tomorrow" is the classic that most vividly expresses this "universal human nature".
The biggest problem with the "best principle" is that the threshold is too high, and it often exceeds the limits of ordinary people's abilities, making the vast majority of people "look at the door and sigh".
Perhaps, the "sub-good principle" is a way to potentially put more ordinary people on the path to relative success.
At the heart of the "sub-good principle" is "lowering the threshold" – it encourages a theory of "small wins become big wins", that is, if you can't do 100, only 1 can do it: because 1 is always greater than 0; If you can't climb Mount Taishan, just climb the small sand dune in front of your house, because it's better than standing still.
In short, as long as you do something, it's better than not doing it.
Because the threshold is greatly reduced, there is more possibility for ordinary people to persist, and as long as everything is adhered to, the probability of success will increase.
It's just that following the "sub-good principle" of success is a little longer.
All in all, the "best principle", although ostensibly in the name of making everyone successful, is ultimately able to motivate, in fact, it is still a minority; The "sub-good principle" can effectively motivate more people and benefit as many people as possible.
The reserves of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake increased by 0.71 million tons this year - Xinhua Net
Xining, 11 Dec (Xinhua) -- Reporters Luo Xiaofei and Zhang Hongxiang learned from the Qinghai Provincial Department of Agriculture and Rural Affairs that the latest monitoring results show that the reserves of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake have increased by 0.71 million tons this year compared with the previous year, reaching 108,500 tons, an increase of more than 40 times compared with the early stage of protection in 2002.
Qinghai Lake naked carp, commonly known as "Huangyu", is a unique and precious fish species in Qinghai Lake, which plays a decisive role in maintaining the safety and biodiversity of the "water-fish-bird" ecological chain in the Qinghai Lake basin.
In the 1960s and 1970s, due to factors such as large-scale hunting by humans and the increasing degradation of the environment in the breeding waters of naked carp, the number of naked carp in Qinghai Lake decreased sharply, and the resource reserves of naked carp in Qinghai Lake were only 2592 tons in 2002.
In 2004, the naked carp of Qinghai Lake was listed as an endangered species in the Red List of Chinese Species.
Since 2003, Qinghai Province has closed the lake to breed fish, prohibiting any unit, collective or individual from fishing naked carp in the main rivers and tributaries of Qinghai Lake and the lake area, and prohibiting the sale of naked carp and its products.
At the same time, through artificial breeding and stocking, cleaning up the main rivers and channels of Qinghai Lake, and designing scientific and reasonable "fish crossing channels" and other measures to continue to increase protection, the reserves of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake have increased year by year.
Yang Lin, deputy director of the Department of Agriculture and Rural Affairs of Qinghai Province, said that as of now, nearly 180 million naked carps in Qinghai Lake have been artificially increased and stocked, and the contribution rate to the recovery of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake has exceeded 23%.
The Sanjiangyuan area of Qinghai is an important ecological barrier and water conservation area in China and even in Asia, while Qinghai Lake is a natural barrier and ecological function area to control the spread of desertification in the west to the east.
In order to protect the ecological environment of the Sanjiangyuan area and the waters of Qinghai Lake, protect aquatic wildlife, and maintain the biodiversity of the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, since the beginning of this year, Qinghai has successively issued a notice on the prohibition of fishing in the key waters of the Yangtze River, the Yellow River and Qinghai Lake, and built a comprehensive ban on fishing management system of "one river, one river and one lake".
